###################################################################################################################
# ATTENTION ALL DOOM SOULS TOUCHING THIS ACCURSED FILE - BE WARNED AND BE AWARE
# READ THIS NOTICE OR ELSE FACE DYNASTIC EXTINCTION - LORD PANZER, KEEPER OF THE BLESSED MAP FILES, DECREES THUSLY!
# IGNORE HIS WORDS AT YOUR OWN PERIL, FOR NOT ONLY DOES HIS BARBED TONGUE CARRY FIRE, BUT HE IS KNOWN TO WHINE AND
# BITCH AT LITERALLY ANYTHING - SO READ THUSLY OR ELSE BEAFEARED OF THE GREAT MOCKERY HE MAY LEVEL UPON YOU!!!!
#
# Titles are organized by Non-Titular and Titular, and then further by region and sub-region for landed titles and
# in somewhat arbitrary categories (by necessity due to variety) for titular. Under these headings, they are sorted
# by alphabetical order.
#
# Please ensure you keep the following in mind at all times:
# 1. Follow the formatting as listed as the above, this is not difficult.
# 2. All titles besides baronies should have a single empty line between them, baronies should be grouped together
# 3. All titles should be sorted by rank, and then alphabetically sorted at the empire level, below that they should 
# be sorted based on order you wish for them to appear in game - namely based on precedence by historical position 
# (IE: Etepezea should come first in Aversaria's governorates).
# 4. Duplicate baronies have a solid chance to cause a CTD. Ensure you are not duplicating the barony's name OR its
# ID.
# 5. The lines with @ give the AI direction on what title should be made their primary one. They are optional.
# 6. Capitals are optional, and will default to the first title under the provinces hierarchy if not provided.
# 7. Missing brackets WILL CAUSE A CTD, ensure you are formatting correctly.
# 8. Ensure any baronies added are not in default.map, consult the mapping guide for regex to do this easily.
# 9. Use INDENTATION AND NOT SPACES! Spaces make regex and other tools more difficult to use. Feel free to copy
# and paste from the below example:
# GOOD:	b_title| BAD:   b_title
# 10. ALL TITLES ARE SPACED BY A TAB FOR EACH ABOVE. This means that empires have no indentation, kingdoms under
# empires do, but kingdoms without an empire do not. Every title below has one more indentation, so if a landed_title
# entry has an empire down to barony, the empire has no indentation, the kingdom has one, the duchy has two, the
# county three, and the barony four. All code within each title should also receive a single indent under it.
# For the love of god please keep this consistent and organized.
#
# PANZY TIP #58159124810: If you mess with landed_titles and suddenly everything is crashing, remove all landed_title
# entries besides a single empire and start the game. If it starts, congrats, its a landed_titles crash! (you can do
# this easily by selecting an empire, (if in Sublime) going to Selection > Invert Selection, and then deleting).
# Want to fix this crash but don't know how you fucked up? Then do Panzer's Patented Tried and True Title Fixing Testing
# Trouble Fix #14™ (copyright pending). Simply move all landed titles to a new text document, paste half of them back in,
# and start the game. No more crash? Than the province is in the half you didn't add, likewise on the reverse. Simply 
# readd the titles back in chunks - first empires then kingdoms etc - until you find the offending barony.
#
# If you tell me you need help with a landed_titles crash and you didn't try this first I will hunt you down.
# xoxoxoxoxoxox - Panzy
###################################################################################################################

	cultural_names = {
		apokiakas = cn_palaiochora
